<h3>Accelerating Increment / Decrement Buttons</h3>

<p>
  This example demonstrates a few different concepts:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>Tricky time-based operations like acceleration are simplified
      by the sequential style of task functions</li>
  <li>
    Tasks integrate with the template actions API: you can use
    <code>taskName.perform</code> in place of anywhere you
    might want to use a classic Ember action name.
  </li>
</ul>

<h5>Live Example</h5>

<h1>Num: {{count}}</h1>

<p>(Hold down the buttons to accelerate.)</p>

{{! BEGIN-SNIPPET press-and-hold-buttons }}
<p>
  {{#press-and-hold-button
    press=(action incrementBy.perform -1)
    release=(action incrementBy.perform 0)}}
      --Decrease
  {{/press-and-hold-button}}

  {{#press-and-hold-button
    press=(action incrementBy.perform 1)
    release=(action incrementBy.perform 0)}}
      Increase++
  {{/press-and-hold-button}}
</p>
{{! END-SNIPPET }}

